#: ../../users_databases.rst:5 0e7f62abd9f0491e90c75547bd179c15
msgid "Users databases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:7 0f0c3f0858e048b2a81aa4ec607ddd38
msgid ""
"NethSecurity introduces support for two types of users databases: a local"
" database and a remote LDAP database, enhancing user management "
"capabilities. Users inside the databases can be used for VPN connections,"
" including the :ref:`openvpn_roadwarrior-section`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:10 c4cf6624190745dc8b8ecce8b1f6a2cd
msgid ""
"Only users with a password can connect to VPN by authenticating with a "
"username and password. Users without a password can connect to VPN by "
"authenticating with a certificate or other authentication methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:14 a566024e02a944e5aa05e6af2201e0ca
msgid "Local database"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:16 1df51a9458a84b8694368998b33e1644
msgid ""
"The local user database is an inherent component of the firewall, "
"ensuring seamless user authentication for VPN services. It is present by "
"default, offering a foundation for user management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:19 1b4a49502afa463e9c88b746d281398b
msgid ""
"To create a new user, click on the :guilabel:`Add user` button to "
"initiate the process. When configuring a local user, you should fill all "
"the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:22 9e1d609e2dcb47f8b4e7f34e8830bce6
msgid "``Username``: specifies the desired username."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:23 f9555be1c6b34e6f8fc0592239c0a1ec
msgid ""
"``Display Name``: specifies the display name of the user. This field is "
"optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:24 298cc46157a3462885da07171ff5d331
msgid ""
"``User password``: specifies the password of the user. This is required "
"only if the VPN is configured to use password authentication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:25 2ce13ff70e1a4efa883a006a0e6fe651
msgid ""
"``Confirm password``: specifies the password of the user, make sure to "
"match the password with the one specified in the previous field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:27 14d37fce5dbb4f03bacedb110c07c167
msgid ""
"The local user database is implemented as UCI configuration file. "
"Passwords of local users are stored in the Unix passwd format, ensuring "
"compatibility and security in the local user database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:30 84eb3f1c0ecb4d429f1ff9d2041f3e12
msgid ""
"Users inside the local database can be granted :ref:`administrative "
"privileges <admin_users-section>` on the web user interface by enabling "
"the ``Administrator user`` option. The user must have a password set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:36 0725fc1baccd4dab87726003194f8e64
msgid "Remote databases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:38 f291cf95727e4bf2a871b6d0de3fe7e1
msgid "Subscription required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:40 1da77963d1834c7ba5fb587573687209
msgid "This feature is available only if the firewall has a valid subscription."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:42 2d0a51cb025e4059b7daf8a4c2a525a2
msgid ""
"The administrator can extend the capabilities of the firewall by adding "
"new remote databases. Users in remote databases must be added directly at"
" the source. User modifications should be made on the underlying LDAP "
"server to accurately reflect changes in the firewall configuration page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:46 dbf0541b7af041feafb302f289bdfb3b
msgid ""
"If the remote database is offline, VPN authentication will fail. It is "
"crucial to ensure that the remote database is online and accessible to "
"ensure proper user authentication through the VPN service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:49 0a0adbbda4ec4bcc998ff5d9e3013994
msgid ""
"When configuring a remote database, click on the :guilabel:`Add remote "
"database` button  and fill all the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:51 f7122d04ff0d4cd9be1a0e51e6e3280e
msgid ""
"``LDAP URI``: specifies the LDAP Uniform Resource Identifier (URI), "
"including the server address and port (e.g., ``ldap://example.com:389``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:53 4dd0f62a41c843398c9737edbba178ba
msgid ""
"``Type``: specifies the type of LDAP server. The available options are "
"``Active Directory`` and ``OpenLDAP``. If OpenLDAP is selected, the "
"remote server should respect the RFC 2307 schema."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:56 5587630de9a745908a321083ffc7e46c
msgid ""
"``Base DN``: specifies the LDAP Base Distinguished Name (DN), "
"representing the starting point for searches in the LDAP directory (eg. "
"``dc=example,dc=com``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:58 e07c44ae64754c86aa95908b806e966a
msgid ""
"``User DN``: specifies the LDAP User Distinguished Name (DN). If not "
"present, the default value is equal to base_dn (eg. "
"``cn=users,dc=example,dc=com``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:60 a7926922d61148ddbd7894b78be382ba
msgid ""
"``User attribute field``: specifies the user attribute used to identify "
"the user, this option is used by the OpenVPN road warrior server to "
"compose the user bind DN. It should be ``cn`` for Active Directory or "
"``uid`` for OpenLDAP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:63 5983b4ba6e5e493e9064acc53dea60ec
msgid ""
"This field is used to authenticate users in the OpenVPN road warrior "
"server. The authentication process is based on a LDAP bind operation "
"which uses the user attribute field to compose the user bind DN with the "
"user DN. Example: given a user named `jdoe` in the OpenLDAP directory, "
"the user bind DN is composed as `uid=jdoe,ou=People,dc=directory,dc=nh`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:68 6296ef0750a84cd9987f766a87ce6c0c
msgid ""
"``User display name field``: specifies the user attribute containing the "
"user's complete name like `John Doe`. Usually is ``cn`` for OpenLDAP and "
"``displayName`` for Active Directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:71 7e812a504b424132b675db8d25a45978
#, python-format
msgid ""
"``Custom user bind DN``: if this field is set, it overrides the "
"calculated user bind DN used to authenticate users in the OpenVPN road "
"warrior server. The field can contain a ``%u`` placeholder which is "
"replaced with the username during the authentication process. Use this "
"setting if you do not know if the user CN field contains the user full "
"name, like ``John Doe``, or the username, like ``jdoe``. If the remote "
"server is an Active Directory server, you can use one of the following "
"values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:76 705ebee6e9da4b148628021ddb0cae6b
#, python-format
msgid ""
"``%u@domain.local``: where `domain.local` is the domain name of the "
"Active Directory server; inside the OpenVPN client, to authenticate the "
"user use only the username like ``jdoe``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:78 aacdf5a98edb4d8e8ab2ea0e283f1c37
#, python-format
msgid ""
"``DOMAIN\\%u``: where `DOMAIN` is the realm of the Active Directory "
"server; inside the OpenVPN client, to authenticate the user use only the "
"username like ``jdoe``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:81 ea080a6901664d6b96817afbcf6af84d
#, python-format
msgid ""
"If the remote server is an OpenLDAP you can leave this field empty or "
"specify it like ``uid=%u,dc=directory,dc=nh``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:83 d14203737f134f9ca9b5fc572b887389
msgid ""
"``Bind DN``: specifies the LDAP Bind Distinguished Name (DN), "
"representing the user used to bind to the LDAP server. For an OpenLDAP "
"server, it's usually something like "
"``uid=ldapservice,dc=directory,dc=nh``, where for an Active Directory "
"server, it's usually something like ``ldapservice@example.com`` or "
"``cn=ldapservice,cn=Users,dc=example,dc=com``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:87 acf1f73fa5854f1bbb923db2d2d5ff2c
msgid ""
"``Bind password``: specifies the password of the user used to bind to the"
" LDAP server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:89 48d81f3581dd486f89888ae61de1ae40
msgid ""
"``StartTLS``: enables StartTLS for secure communication with the LDAP "
"server, it should be disabled if the LDAP URI is already using the "
"``ldaps://`` scheme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:91 c60feea50d9d4cb7894dca5092e7b930
msgid ""
"``Verify TLS certificate``: determines whether to enable or disable "
"certificate validation, it must be disabled if the LDAP server is using a"
" self-signed certificate."
msgstr ""

